THE Ga-Rankuwa police in Tshwane recovered human remains on Wednesday, 19 May. According to police spokesman Matthews Nkoadi, they were called to the scene by a passersby who found the remains of an elderly person in Santos Valley next to a railway station. He said preliminary investigations revealed that the body might have been lying there over some time since only the bones were visible. “These remains have been picked up for further information and results will assist in identifying it. “An inquest docket has been opened for further investigation,” he said. Nkoadi said anyone with information that might assist the police with the identity or who might know somebody who went missing for the past few months in that area is requested to contact CrimeStop on 08600 10111, or MySAPS App. All information will be treated anonymously.